ZH: 通货膨胀是一个国家货币持续失去购买力的过程。
EN: Inflation is the process of a country's currency continuously losing purchasing power.

ZH: 由于通货膨胀，这家超市的物品价格涨得飞快。
EN: Due to inflation, prices of items in this supermarket are rising rapidly.

ZH: 通货膨胀也会导致工资的实际价值下降。
EN: Inflation can also lead to a decrease in the real value of wages.

ZH: 近几个月来，通货膨胀率已经超过了政府的目标。
EN: In the past few months, the inflation rate has surpassed the government's target.

ZH: 通货膨胀对经济发展有着深远的影响。
EN: Inflation has profound effects on economic development.

ZH: 许多国家都在努力控制通货膨胀的速度。
EN: Many countries are working to control the speed of inflation.

ZH: 通货膨胀可以加剧贫富差距。
EN: Inflation can exacerbate the wealth gap.

ZH: 近年来，通货膨胀一直是我们经济的主要挑战。
EN: In recent years, inflation has been a major challenge for our economy.

ZH: 政府采取了一些措施来减缓通货膨胀的速度。
EN: The government has taken some measures to slow down the pace of inflation.

ZH: 通货膨胀可能会对人民的生活造成影响。
EN: Inflation may have an impact on people's lives.

ZH: 通货膨胀会使得购买力下降。
EN: Inflation will reduce purchasing power.

ZH: 过度印钞会导致通货膨胀。
EN: Excessive money printing can lead to inflation.

ZH: 通货膨胀使得人们更难以维持生活水平。
EN: Inflation makes it more difficult for people to maintain their standard of living.

ZH: 通货膨胀经常被认为是经济问题的一种表现。
EN: Inflation is often seen as a manifestation of economic issues.

ZH: 有时候，通货膨胀可以刺激经济增长。
EN: Sometimes, inflation can stimulate economic growth.

ZH: 通货膨胀率的增加可能引发需求的下降。
EN: An increase in the inflation rate may lead to a decrease in demand.

ZH: 针对通货膨胀问题，政府需要采取更有力的措施。
EN: The government needs to take stronger measures to address the issue of inflation.

ZH: 通货膨胀对固定收入家庭的影响更为严重。
EN: Inflation has a more severe impact on households with fixed incomes.

ZH: 媒体经常报道关于通货膨胀的最新数据。
EN: The media often reports the latest data on inflation.

ZH: 通货膨胀可能会影响储蓄的实际价值。
EN: Inflation may affect the real value of savings.
